🧸 Pokémon Plushy Protocol v1.0

“Photo → Persona → Team → Scene → Image”

⸻

🔷 1. INPUT LAYER (Perception)

Input: Any image with a person (or people)

What gets extracted:

* Age range (baby / toddler / teen / adult)
* Emotion (joy, calm, chaos, pride, etc.)
* Context (birthday, beach, couch, playtime, etc.)
* Energy level (still vs active vs chaotic)
* Role (leader, caregiver, explorer, etc.)

This is NOT identity recognition
It’s vibe + pattern inference

⸻

🔷 2. PERSONA SYNTHESIS (Compression)

Convert observations into a simple 3–5 trait profile

Example outputs:

* “Joyful chaos + curiosity + snack-driven” (baby)
* “Playful explorer + imagination + movement” (kid)
* “Grounded warmth + balance + leadership” (adult)

Formula:

Persona = Emotion + Behavior + Context + Energy

⸻

🔷 3. TEAM GENERATION (Mapping Engine)

Rules:

* 6 Pokémon max
* Age-appropriate scaling:
    * Baby → baby Pokémon
    * Toddler → cute/simple forms
    * Adult → more evolved / elegant forms

Matching Logic:

Each Pokémon represents:

* A trait
* A role
* A visual match (color/energy/style)

