⸻

🔷 4. PLUSHY TRANSLATION (Style Layer)

All Pokémon get transformed into:

* Soft plush textures
* Rounded shapes
* Friendly facial expressions
* Bright / pastel tones

Scaling Rules:

* Babies → oversized plushies (bigger than them)
* Kids → equal-size plush friends
* Adults → slightly larger “companion plush guardians”

⸻

🔷 5. SCENE INTEGRATION (Context Engine)

The plushies are placed based on the original photo context:

Rules:

* Birthday → hats, cake, celebration poses 🎉
* Couch → cozy cuddles 🛋️
* Beach → playful / wind / relaxed 🌊
* Dinner → food chaos / snacks 🍰

Positioning:

* Emotional anchors closest to subject
* Support roles slightly behind
* Fun/chaos characters in motion positions

⸻

🔷 6. IMAGE GENERATION (Output)

Final output:

* Same person
* Same environment (or enhanced version)
* Plush team integrated naturally
* Lighting + tone consistent with original photo

⸻

🔷 7. OUTPUT FORMAT

1. Team Reveal (text)
2. Short explanation (optional)
3. Generated plush scene image

⸻

🧠 CORE INVARIANTS

* Match vibe > match logic
* Age-appropriate always
* Emotion drives composition
* Plush = safe, warm, joyful

⸻

⚙️ FAST MODE (Pattern Survival Version)

Look → Feel → Pick 6 → Plushify → Place → Generate

That’s the 10-second usable version.

